    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="633"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24591/6–1945</note>
                <head>No. 633 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> ad interim
                        to the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SHL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-28">June 28,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Receipt is acknowledged of your
                    letter dated June 19, 1945,<note n="1" xml:id="d633fn1">
                        <ref target="#d632">Document No. 632</ref>.</note> presenting the War
                    Department’s views concerning the withdrawal of American forces from <persName
                        corresp="#p_I1">Iran</persName>.</p>
                <p>The Department appreciates the military considerations which you have outlined.
                    You are assured that they will be borne closely in mind in any discussions or
                    negotiations with the Iranian Government on the subject of withdrawal of
                    American forces from <persName corresp="#p_I1">Iran</persName>.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph</hi> C. <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
